[1] Russia (Udmutria)
Date: Tue 10 Apr 2012
Source: The Moscow Post [In Russian, machine trans. edited]
http://moscow-post.ru/news/society/v_izhevske_zafiksirovana_vspyshka_kori53278/

Outbreak of measles in Izhevsk city
-----------------------------
An outbreak of measles virus infection has been reported In Izhevsk. So far 15 cases of suspected measles have been admitted to the Clinical Hospital of Infectious Diseases. Fourteen are currently undergoing treatment. Six of the cases have been confirmed by laboratory tests. One patient has recovered and has already been discharged from hospital.

Anti-epidemic measures are being enforced in the outbreak area. All contacts of the affected patients are being vaccinated, as are those who have not received measles vaccination previously.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Measles outbreaks are continuing to spread across the Russian Federation. Izhevsk is the capital city of the Republic of Udmurtria. Izhevsk city is situated on the Izh river in the Western Urals. The population numbers around 640 000.

A similar report in Life Newshttp://www.lifenews.ru/news/88183 states that all the patients are aged between 20 and 50, and the number of direct contacts being screened is approximately 500.

The location of Izhevsk can be seen in the interactive map at: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Izhevsk. - Mod.CP]


