[4] USA (Illinois)
Date: Thu 12 Apr 2012
Source: myststline.com [edited]
http://mystateline.com/fulltext-news?nxd_id=330112

Potential Measles Case at Kinnikinnick School District
---------------------------------------------
ROSCOE: Students and parents are on alert over a potential case of measles at Ledgewood School in the Kinnikinnick School District.

The Health Department cautions this is only a suspected case. But, since measles is so contagious, they had to notify families. Some symptoms include fever, cough, runny nose, red eyes, and rashes. School administrators won't give any details about the case, but expect test results within the next few days. Until then, kids who haven't received measles vaccine are asked to stay home for the next three weeks

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There are four schools in the unspoiled hill country along the Rock River. Ledgewood School in the Kinnikinnick School District is one of four schools in the district offer personalised instruction in small school settings. Roscoe is located in the county of Winnebago which can be located in the map to the counties of Illnois at: http://geology.com/state-map/illinois.shtml.

As of Sun 15 Apr 2012 there has been nbo confirmation of the suspected case of measles- at at Ledgewood School in the Kinnikinnick School District. - Mod.CP]


